            <div class="paragraph_content">
              <b>Serving Opportunities at Open Heavens</b>
            </div>

            <div class="paragraph_content">
              <b>A FEW OF THE MANY AREAS OF OPPORTUNITY IN WHICH YOU CAN SERVE IN OUR CHURCH</b>
            </div>

            <div class="paragraph_content">Part of being a healthy, thriving and organically growing local church family is for everyone to be actively involved. Take a minute to look through our various opportunities to be part of the incredible and talented volunteers. We’re confident that you’ll find a place to flourish!</div>

            <div class="paragraph_content">Open Heavens Christian Centre offers several unique opportunities for you to use your God-given gifts, passions and talents to help develop the local church and impact our community. You can invest your time and skills in our children and youth activities, help to welcome our guests and make them feel comfortable, help care for the worship spaces and facilities, make and serve coffee to guests and members to enhance fellowship at the foyer and much more. Whatever your passion, we have a place for you to explore and flourish at Open Heavens.</div>

            <div class="paragraph_content">There are several opportunities here to make a difference with your time, from volunteering in a role that fits your gifts, interests and talents to even pioneering a ministry through your own creativity and innovation. Find the opportunity you are interested in, then simply email the staff contact and let them know.</div>

            <div class="paragraph_content">Still thinking of where to serve? Please fill out this form with your interest areas, skills, etc. and a staff member or ministry leader will follow up with you. Maybe you already have inspired ideas that need support and encouragement to implement? Fill out the ministry idea form here and the relevant ministry leader will get in touch with you during the week. </div>

            <div class="paragraph_content">Once you click and fill out the forms next to your preferred serving opportunity, the relevant ministry leaders will be in contact with you about volunteering. Thank you for being a part of our local church family and for deciding to lend your time, abilities and heart to the vision of Open Heavens.</div>

            <div class="paragraph_content">
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <b><%= link_to "Prayer", "#", class: "weblink" %></b>
                  <span>here are opportunities to serve through praying with guests after weekend services or participating in weekly intercessory/ministry network prayers or praying over requests that come through the church prayer box or website.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b><%= link_to "Children’s Services", "#", class: "weblink" %></b>
                  <span>(helping to create a loving, safe and clean environment for Open Heavens children, their parents and carers).</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b><%= link_to "First Impression Hosts ", "#", class: "weblink" %></b>
                  <span>(parking marshals, greeters, ushers). This is an opportunity to help deliver excellent guest experience while enhancing overall service ambience. Serve in the Open Heavens lobby area or main auditorium, welcoming and assisting in delivering an excellent ambience and experience to our visitors and members as we seek to glorify God through our weekly worship services. This includes assisting with seating, collecting the offering, handing out service items, locating the right classes, etc. This naturally sits with the OHCC First Impressions ministry.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b><%= link_to "Care Centre ", "#", class: "weblink" %></b>
                  <span>(member and community care, providing coffee and snacks for services and events). There are several opportunities at Open Heavens to help create a radically inclusive community where people are treated with love and care regardless of their ethnic, economic or legal status through the core values of dignity, hope and transformation.</span><br/><br/>
                  <span>From routine visits to members to supporting those going through various challenges, and from stocking groceries at the food bank a few hours a week to offering legal consultation to members with challenging life and career issues such as immigration, the Open Heavens care volunteers live out the compassion and justice mission by sharing the hope and love of Christ while meeting basic needs and offering short- and long-term solutions that empower people towards a more stable future.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b><%= link_to "Admin and Financial Stewardship", "#", class: "weblink" %></b>
                  <span>Depending on skills and preferences, you may serve as a church office support volunteer providing assistance for various administrative and finance-related task. This might also mean serving in the counting team, a wonderful team of volunteers that helps count the offering during our weekend services. It may also extend to welcome and registration of attendance at services, training and meetings, offering general membership support and providing information to members during services.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b><%= link_to "IT / Data Quality Analysts / Hardware Support ", "#", class: "weblink" %></b>
                  <span>Help with church computers – do you enjoy working with computers, networking, software and electronics support? Open Heavens have room in the church office and across the network for volunteers with relevant skills to assist our technical team with some basic computer support and related tasks.</span><br/><br/>
                  <span>If you enjoy analytics, there are opportunities to serve as a data quality analyst and also help the church office team update records and make the best use of our new church management systems.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b><%= link_to "Stewardship Coach", "#", class: "weblink" %></b>
                  <span>Changing lives by serving as a community budget coach, organising community-focused seminars or meeting one-to-one with people who need guidance and assistance in putting together a budget or training support towards good stewardship of their finances.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b><%= link_to "Facilities Management and Logistics ", "#", class: "weblink" %></b>
                  <span>(custodial champions, facilities care and various logistic and events support services). The custodial support champions are responsible for the appearance, maintenance and security of the Open Heavens Christian Centre buildings and their contents, external equipment and facilities. We are always looking for help and input from those with experience in the building trade or other related fields.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b><%= link_to "Service Preparation and Special Events Logistics", "#", class: "weblink" %></b>
                  <span>(help with coordinating services, special events and programmes). You can apply your organisational skills by participating in the planning and execution of high-quality services and events in our church that will help people worship and learn about God’s word in an excellent distraction-free environment. We always need your event and project management skills in order to make our weekend worship services and special events run excellently and to the glory of God through proper planning, support and execution of all the various elements.</span><br/><br/>
                  <span>Preparing various sections of our facilities (set up and tear down) ahead of services, so as to provide a welcoming and loving environment for fellowship to occur by organising spaces for various gatherings and users of facilities. This also involves caring for the facilities as good stewards of the resources that God has provided for our comfort.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b><%= link_to "Sanctuary Cleaning and Decor", "#", class: "weblink" %></b>
                  <span>You can join a group of wonderful volunteers regularly helping to keep the interior of the facilities clean and sparkling, or prepare interior spaces for special events and services, e.g. Christmas, Easter, etc.</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b><%= link_to "Technical Support ", "#", class: "weblink" %></b>
                  <span>Serve with the team of volunteers who are responsible for vehicle care and equipment repair. Depending on availability and your flexibility, you can utilise your mechanical skills to help with church vehicle and equipment repairs, as well as preventative maintenance of both vehicles and all church facilities in general.</span><br/><br/>
